GTTM_Analyser

Class TimeSpanReductionAnalyser

  • java.lang.Object
    • GTTM_Analyser.TimeSpanReductionAnalyser

  • public class TimeSpanReductionAnalyser
extends java.lang.Object
    A singleton class that provides assessment of the time-span reduction preference rules. At the moment this class provides implementations for TSPR2 and TSPR3.

      • getTSPR2andTSPR3

        public double getTSPR2andTSPR3(AttackEvent parent,
                               AttackEvent child,
                               Scale localScale)
        Generates a rating based on the combination of TSPR2 and TSPR3 rules, reflecting the weightings of the different rules.
        Parameters:
        parent - the AttackEvent to be judged as belonging to the parent branch of the child AttackEvent
        child - the AttackEvent under consideration for its relation to the parent AttackEvent
        localScale - the local scale against which to consider the child AttackEvent's relation to the tonic
        Returns:
        a rating based on how strongly the given parent Beat rates as a parent branch of the child Beat. A rating towards 1.0 indicates a strong relation according to TSPR2 and TSPR3 combined. A rating towards 0.0 indicates a very weak relation. A rating near to 0.5 indicates a mild relation.

      • assessTSPR2

        public double assessTSPR2(AttackEvent parent,
                          AttackEvent child,
                          Scale localScale)
        Assesses how preferable the proposed child AttackEvent would constitute a child branch of the branch associated with the proposed parent AttackEvent. This takes into consideration the consonance of the child event with the proposed parent, and the relation to the local tonic of the two events. A child branch which is relatively consonant with the given parent AttackEvent and relative further away from the tonic than the given parent AttackEvent is preferred.
        Parameters:
        parent - the AttackEvent to be judged as belonging to the parent branch of the child AttackEvent
        child - the AttackEvent under consideration for its relation to the parent AttackEvent
        localScale - the local scale against which to consider the child AttackEvent's relation to the tonic
        Returns:
        a rating based on how strongly the given parent Beat rates as a parent branch of the child Beat. A rating towards 1.0 indicates a strong relation according to TSPR2. A rating towards 0.0 indicates a very weak relation. A rating near to 0.5 indicates a mild relation.

      • assessTSPR3a

        public double assessTSPR3a(AttackEvent parent,
                           AttackEvent child)
        Assesses how preferable a proposed parent AttackEvent constitutes the parent branch of a given child AttackEvent by assessing how strongly the given parent event constitutes a higher melodic pitch than the given child event.
        Parameters:
        parent - the AttackEvent to be judged as belonging to the parent branch of the child AttackEvent
        child - the AttackEvent under consideration for its relation to the parent AttackEvent
        Returns:
        a rating based on how strongly the given child Beat rates as a child branch of the parent Beat. A rating towards 1.0 indicates a strong preference according to TSPR3a. A rating towards 0.0 indicates a very weak preference. A rating near to 0.5 indicates a mild preference.

      • assessConsonance

        public double assessConsonance(AttackEvent parent,
                               AttackEvent child)
        Assesses the consonance between two given AttackEvents objects. For use in identifying how well two AttackEvents are related to each other. A high rating indicates a high preference. A low rating indicates negative preference.
        Parameters:
        parent - an AttackEvent to be judged as a potential parent of the child event
        child - an AttackEvent to judge the consonance with the proposed parent AttackEvent.
        Returns:
        a rating between 0.0 and 1.0. A rating towards 1.0 indicates a high preference. A rating towards 0.0 indicates a very low preference.

      • assessTonicRelationBetweenEvents

        public double assessTonicRelationBetweenEvents(AttackEvent parent,
                                               AttackEvent child,
                                               Scale localTonic)
        Assesses whether the proposed parent AttackEvent has a higher relation to the given Scale's tonic than the proposed child AttackEvent.
        Parameters:
        parent - proposed parent AttackEvent
        child - proposed child AttackEvent
        localTonic - the Scale against which to assess the tonic relation
        Returns:
        a rating indicating whether the parent AttackEvent has a higher relation to the tonic or not. A rating towards 1.0 indicates that the parent AttackEvent is more closely related to the tonic. A rating towards 0.0 indicates that the child AttackEvent is more closely related to the tonic. A rating of 0.5 indicates that both AttackEvents have the same relational value to the tonic.

      • assessTonicRelation

        public double assessTonicRelation(AttackEvent child,
                                  Scale localScale)
        Assesses the strength of the relation of a given AttackEvent to the local tonic.
        Parameters:
        child - AttackEvent to be assessed.
        localScale - The Scale against which to judge how closely the given AttackEvent is related to the tonic.
        Returns:
        a rating between 1.0 and 0.0. A rating towards 1.0 indicates high relationship, and a rating towards 0.0 indicates a low relationship.
